        "content": "<p>Is there a reason <code>finset.sigma</code> is defined in mathlib but <code>set.sigma</code> isn't?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/data/finset/basic.html#finset.sigma\">https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/data/finset/basic.html#finset.sigma</a></p>",
        "id": 232315341,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Nelson",
        "timestamp": 1617043202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nobody needed it? <code>def set.sigma {α : Type*} {β : α → Type*} (s : set α) (t : α → set β) := {x : Σ a, β a | x.1 ∈ s ∧ x.2 ∈ t x.1}</code></p>",
        "id": 232316052,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1617043488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yup - that's what I've been using. With <code>finsum</code> it will likely be useful for lemmas like <code>finsum_in_sigma</code> that reverse the order of summation.</p>",
        "id": 232316192,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Nelson",
        "timestamp": 1617043540
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Was just making sure there isn't a better reason</p>",
        "id": 232316246,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Nelson",
        "timestamp": 1617043561
    },
    {
